name: Palindrome
description:
Given a string s, determine if it contains any palindrome of length exactly
100 as a subsequence. If it has any, print any one of them. If it doesn't have
any, print a palindrome that is a subsequence of s and is as long as possible.
Input The only line of the input contains one string s of length n (1 ≤ n ≤
5·10^4) containing only lowercase English letters. Output If s contains a
palindrome of length exactly 100 as a subsequence, print any palindrome of
length 100 which is a subsequence of s. If s doesn't contain any palindromes
of length exactly 100, print a palindrome that is a subsequence of s and is as
long as possible. If there exists multiple answers, you are allowed to print
any of them. Examples Input bbbabcbbb Output bbbcbbb Input
rquwmzexectvnbanemsmdufrg Output rumenanemur Note A subsequence of a string is
a string that can be derived from it by deleting some characters without
changing the order of the remaining characters. A palindrome is a string that
reads the same forward or backward.
